In this environment, we believe that ' Driving Progress 2023 ' and its underlying assumptions are focused on supporting to support our business resilience and continue growing our business sustainably. As a result, in 2021, AXA has been consistently executing its strategy with strong delivery across its five strategic priorities:

- 1) Expand Health and Protection: (i)/uni00A0solid global growth in Health business of 5% in 2021, (ii)/uni00A0Digital Health Platform (DHP) providing health services within seamless end-to-end healthcare journeys deployed in 5 European countries, and (iii)/uni00A0on-going execution of our vertical integration strategy, organically (Italy, Egypt, Mexico, Nigeria) as well as inorganically (Spain with GIC (5) acquisition);
- 2) Simplify customer experience and accelerate efficiency: (i)/uni00A0NPS (6) reaching 97% above market average, (ii)/uni00A0digital platforms rolling out ( e.g. , Emma app launched in 6 Asian countries, Angel.fr), (iii)/uni00A0ongoing digitalization of the customer journeys in all entities, (iv)/uni00A0turning of our proprietary distribution channels into a fully 'phygital' model, and (v)/uni00A0acceleration on e/ff iciency and product simplification ( e.g. , via cloudification, IT legacy decommissioning, straightthrough processing, and organisational simplification);
- 3) Strengthen underwriting performance: (i)/uni00A0 technical excellence with 2021 Property & Casualty combined ratio at 94.6%, improved by a strong price-increase strategy and successful re-underwriting measures at AXA XL, and (ii)/uni00A0AXA XL turnaround delivered with enhanced underwriting results and reduced earnings' volatility;

